SCREENSHOT: 03-expired-token.png
=================================
HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
X-Powered-By: Express
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8

Request: GET /api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpZCI6IjEyMyIsImVtYWlsIjoidXNlckB0ZXN0LmNvbSIsInJvbGUiOiJ1c2VyIiwiaWF0IjoxNzc4NzMzNjU0LCJleHAiOjE3Nzg2NDcyNTR9.6DZ_IZSCK9QjlNDJX9EDEdljHVTYOLs0RJk-UPJoWEs
(Token created with -1 day expiry, now expired)

Response:
{
  "message": "Invalid or expired token."
}

Status: 401 Unauthorized
Expected: 401 Unauthorized ✅ PASS

The middleware correctly rejects an expired token because:
1. jwt.verify() checks the 'exp' claim in the token
2. Current time is past the expiration time
3. jwt.verify() throws an error, caught in the catch block
4. 401 response returned (never allows expired token through)
